==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tractarian
<hw>Trac*ta"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Ch. of
England)</fld> <def>One of the writers of the Oxford tracts, called
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Tracts</xex> for the Times,⟦rdquo⟧ issued during the period
1833-1841, in which series of papers the sacramental system and
authority of the Church, and the value of tradition, were brought into
prominence. Also, a member of the High Church party, holding generally
the principles of the Tractarian writers; a Puseyite.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1525 -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tractarian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tractarian
<hw>Trac*ta"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining
to the Tractarians, or their principles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tractarianism</ent>⟦br⟧
